Trendo Privacy Policy
Trendo offers a variety of measures to protect your privacy when you use Trendo Services, including Trendo Sites, Trendo Software, and/or other Trendo Services, etc. Trendo has created this Data Privacy Policy ("Policy") which elaborates upon our privacy practices in order to make our users understand that how Personal Data of users "information" is collected, used, transferred through our websites and mobile applications ("Platform") and Users rights to their information who browse or access the Platform or provide any information to the Platform in regards to its services.
Any references in this Policy to "Trendo", "Company", "we", "our", "us" etc. will be interpreted as a reference to Trendo and any reference to as "Users", "You" or "Yours" is reference to user/ player of this app/ Platform. Whether you are new to Trendo or a long-time user, please do take the time to get to know our practices, and if you have any questions please feel free to contact us.
1. Collection and Use of Information
1.1
The Trendo community will collect your personally identifiable information when you register a Trendo community account, use other Trendo community products or services, access Trendo community webpages, or participate in promotional or prize winning games. The Trendo community also collects personally identifiable information from our business partners.
1.2
When you register a Trendo community account, we will ask for your name, email address, interests, birthday, gender,  photo, Region, Phone Number, bank information, and personal webpage, in addition to a personal profile etc. Once you are successfully registered with the Trendo community, we will be able to identify you when you log in to the server.
1.3
The Trendo community automatically receives and records the information on your browser and server logs, including your IP address, information in the Trendo community cookies and your browsing history.
1.4
In addition, we may collect information from you, including but not limited to:
Software Information, such as Application Version, System Version and application list; Hardware Information, such as IMEI, model info, manufacturer; Network Information, such as IP address, Mobile Network Operator, Network Status; Setting and Usage, such as language preference, time and time zone, errors and reports, browsing history, settings, typing in the URL bar; Location, with your permission; Gyroscope sensor data during shooting; Your phone and social Information you post to Trendo including, but not limited to, threads and comments you post in forums.
1.5
The Trendo community uses this information to enhance the quality of the services that we provide and to improve the effectiveness to better tailor our services to your interests and needs.
2. Disclosure and Sharing of Information
2.1
When you submit the information, it shall be deemed as your consent to the Trendo community regarding the collection, storage, use and disclosure of your personal information by the Trendo community. The Trendo community will never display, rent or sell your personally identifiable information to others.
2.2
The following circumstances are excluded:
(1) When your desired products and services can only be provided if your personal information is disclosed;
(2) When we are required to provide information to the companies that provide products or services on our behalf; (unless we notify you otherwise, these companies do not have the right to use your personally identifiable information);
(3) When we are required to comply with a court summons, court order or to comply with a legal process;
(4) When we discover that you have violated the terms of use of the Trendo community, Trendo community global village or any other products or services.
2.3 The Trendo community is not responsible for any collection, disclosure and/or use of your personal information provided by you to any third party's website which may be linked to or from our website.
