4. Account Deletion Agreement
How to Delete Your Trendo Account?
You may delete your account through [Me – Settings – DeleteAccount]. We will process it for you as soon as possible within 7days after receiving your cancellation application and verifying your identity. After your account is deleted, your personal information will be removed from the Trendo App, except for the personal information that we must retain as explicitly required by laws. For connecting, user disabling, or logging out from your Facebook (Meta)/Google connect credentials to us, all of your profile content and other information may be deleted upon deletion request. Trendo will log out the user from all their user accounts on Trendo and reset all user data. We will also disassociate your username, password, and all related information files and user content associated with or inside your account (or any part thereof), including your user content. However, certain details are maintained with us for archival and legal purposes. Trendo will not have any liability whatsoever to you for any termination, suspension, or deletion of your user content. Trendo will hold and use the content/data as long as required and permissible under local laws. All provisions of the Agreement which should survive shall, including without limitation, warranty disclaimers, governing law, and limitations of liability.
4.1
What happens if I delete my Trendo account?
You won't be able to reactivate or use your Trendo account.Your profile, photos, videos, messages, comments, likes, shares,levels, followers, privileges, and digital contents (Diamondsand Coins) will be permanently deleted and can't be retrieved.
4.2
Who may initiate a request to delete my Trendo account?
In order to initiate a request to delete your Trendo account, you
          will need to meet all of the following requirements:
● Your account is under normal operation. We can't handle requests
          for accounts that are hacked or compromised or involve fraudulent or
          illegal activities.
● There are no large amounts of unconsumed or unwithdrawn assets in
          the account; large virtual assets such as Diamonds and Coins must be
          consumed or withdrawn first.
● You are not a self-media producer or a content creator engaging in
          a separate agreement with us.
● You are free from complaints, controversies, or disputes with us
          or any other third party because of your use of Trendo Services.
4.3
Can I cancel my account deletion?
You can cancel your account deletion if it's within 7 days since you
          initiated the deletion request. After 7 days, your account and all
          your information will be permanently deleted, and you won't be able
          to retrieve your information.
Additional Information:
● During our handling of your deletion request, we have the right to
          suspend your request without obtaining your permission if your
          account is reported or investigated by any other users or
          governmental body, or is otherwise related to any legal proceeding.
● Requesting to delete your Trendo account will not free you from
          any obligation or duty, regardless of monetary or not, arising from
          your previous use of Trendo Services.
● You should back up any information you would like to keep;
          otherwise, you may not be able to re-access the information in your
          Trendo account after it is deleted.
● Your information may remain after your account is deleted in
          backup storage that we use to recover in the event of a disaster,
          software error, or other data loss event. We may also keep your
          information for things like legal issues, terms violations, or harm
          prevention efforts.
Please ensure that you've reviewed the document for consistency and
          legal compliance, especially with data protection laws and user
          agreements specific to your service.
